-{"id":"flywheel_gateway-o6n","title":"Enhance WebSocket error messages with hints and examples","description":"# Task: Enhance WebSocket Error Messages with Hints and Examples

## Parent Epic
[Epic] WebSocket UX Improvements (flywheel_gateway-ynm)

## Objective
Improve WebSocket error messages to include helpful hints, examples, and documentation links.

## Current State (ws/handlers.ts)
```typescript
const errorMsg: ServerMessage = {
  type: "error",
  code: "INVALID_FORMAT",
  message: "Invalid message format",
};
```

## Target State
```typescript
const errorMsg: ServerMessage = {
  type: "error",
  code: "INVALID_FORMAT",
  message: "Invalid message format",
  hint: "Messages must be valid JSON with a 'type' field",
  example: { type: "subscribe", channel: "agent:output:AGENT_ID" },
  docs: "https://docs.flywheel.dev/websocket#message-format",
};
```

## Implementation

### 1. Update ErrorMessage Type (ws/messages.ts)
```typescript
export interface ErrorMessage {
  type: "error";
  code: string;
  message: string;
  channel?: string;
  details?: Record<string, unknown>;
  /** Suggested action to resolve the error */
  hint?: string;
  /** Example of valid input/usage */
  example?: unknown;
  /** Link to documentation */
  docs?: string;
}
```

### 2. Create WebSocket Error Hints Map
```typescript
// apps/gateway/src/ws/error-hints.ts

export interface WSErrorHint {
  hint: string;
  example?: unknown;
  docs?: string;
}

export const WS_ERROR_HINTS: Record<string, WSErrorHint> = {
  INVALID_FORMAT: {
    hint: "Messages must be valid JSON with a 'type' field",
    example: { type: "subscribe", channel: "agent:output:YOUR_AGENT_ID" },
    docs: "https://docs.flywheel.dev/websocket#message-format",
  },

  INVALID_CHANNEL: {
    hint: "Channel format is 'scope:type:id', e.g., 'agent:output:agent-123'",
    example: "agent:output:agent-abc123",
    docs: "https://docs.flywheel.dev/websocket#channels",
  },

  FORBIDDEN: {
    hint: "You don't have permission to access this channel. Check your authentication.",
    docs: "https://docs.flywheel.dev/websocket#authentication",
  },

  CURSOR_EXPIRED: {
    hint: "The cursor has expired. Reconnect without a cursor to get the latest messages.",
    example: { type: "subscribe", channel: "agent:output:agent-123" },
  },

  RATE_LIMITED: {
    hint: "You're sending messages too fast. Slow down and retry.",
    docs: "https://docs.flywheel.dev/websocket#rate-limits",
  },
};
```

### 3. Update Error Creation in Handlers
```typescript
// ws/handlers.ts

function createWSError(
  code: string,
  message: string,
  channel?: string
): ErrorMessage {
  const hint = WS_ERROR_HINTS[code];

  return {
    type: "error",
    code,
    message,
    ...(channel && { channel }),
    ...(hint?.hint && { hint: hint.hint }),
    ...(hint?.example && { example: hint.example }),
    ...(hint?.docs && { docs: hint.docs }),
  };
}

// Usage
const errorMsg = createWSError("INVALID_FORMAT", "Invalid message format");
ws.send(serializeServerMessage(errorMsg));
```

### 4. Enhance Connected Message
```typescript
// Enhance the welcome message
const connectedMsg: ServerMessage = {
  type: "connected",
  connectionId: connectionId,
  serverTime: new Date().toISOString(),
  serverVersion: BUILD_INFO.version,
